From: Joey Eamigh <55670930+JoeyEamigh@users.noreply.github.com>
Subject: [PATCH] amlogic-meson64: rename MACHINE_FEATURES_BACKFILL_CONSIDERED

Bitbake's wrynose-era oe-core renamed the variable for opting a machine
out of automatic feature backfills from MACHINE_FEATURES_BACKFILL_CONSIDERED
to MACHINE_FEATURES_OPTED_OUT. The deprecated name now triggers a parse-
time error rather than a warning, so the include must be updated for
wrynose to parse.

Signed-off-by: Joey Eamigh <55670930+JoeyEamigh@users.noreply.github.com>
Upstream-Status: Pending
---
diff --git a/conf/machine/include/amlogic-meson64.inc b/conf/machine/include/amlogic-meson64.inc
index 0000000..1111111 100644
--- a/conf/machine/include/amlogic-meson64.inc
+++ b/conf/machine/include/amlogic-meson64.inc
@@ -2,7 +2,7 @@

 require conf/machine/include/amlogic-meson.inc

-MACHINE_FEATURES_BACKFILL_CONSIDERED = "rtc"
+MACHINE_FEATURES_OPTED_OUT = "rtc"

 SOC_FAMILY = "amlogic:meson-gx"
 require conf/machine/include/soc-family.inc
